ZH: 这片土地很荒，几乎没有人烟。
EN: This land is very desolate, with hardly any people around.

ZH: 荒原上的野兽在夜晚出没。
EN: Wild beasts roam the desolate wilderness at night.

ZH: 这个城镇因为水源荒了而被迫搬迁。
EN: The town had to be relocated because of the drought.

ZH: 荒漠中的植物适应了干旱的环境。
EN: The plants in the desert have adapted to the arid conditions.

ZH: 这座城市被疫情所荒废。
EN: The city was abandoned due to the epidemic.

ZH: 老房子里显得异常荒凉。
EN: The old house felt unusually desolate.

ZH: 荒海中的船只无人驾驶。
EN: The ships in the deserted sea were unmanned.

ZH: 地下城内弥漫着荒凉的气息。
EN: The underground city was filled with a desolate atmosphere.

ZH: 荒山中有着神秘的传说。
EN: The desolate mountain is filled with mysterious legends.

ZH: 城市街头因为疫情而显得荒凉。
EN: The city streets seemed deserted due to the epidemic.

ZH: 荒漠中生存的动物有着顽强的生命力。
EN: The animals surviving in the desert have a strong will to live.

ZH: 在冬天，森林显得冷清而荒凉。
EN: In winter, the forest appears bleak and desolate.

ZH: 沼泽地的周围荒无一人。
EN: There is no one around the desolate marshland.

ZH: 荒废的建筑中弥漫着尘土的味道。
EN: The abandoned building was filled with the smell of dust.

ZH: 荒野中的一块石头成为了我的庇护所。
EN: A lone rock in the wilderness became my refuge.

ZH: 荒野里有许多未被探索的秘密。
EN: There are many unexplored mysteries in the wilderness.

ZH: 荒漠中没有生命的迹象。
EN: There is no sign of life in the desert.

ZH: 荒凉的地方适合发展旅游业。
EN: Desolate areas are suitable for tourism development.

ZH: 荒地上长满了杂草和灌木。
EN: The barren land is covered with weeds and bushes.
